{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c585cb64-d133-486c-9506-010b7377bc6b","content":"`.testsettings` files are **not supported** by MSTest v3 — you need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file. Here's what your `local.testsettings` configures:\n\n1. **Test timeout** (30 s)\n2. **Code coverage** data collector\n3. **Assembly resolution** (not needed in modern MSTest — `bin` output is used directly)\n\nLet me create the equivalent `.runsettings`:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_MLBGKV4v9hojVCkadkgIl1","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Creating runsettings migration"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_w9jWPO043Pyv7nvPbLSk7T","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-32e0c05c3c62451e964aaa33200c5fb6/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <!-- Replaces <Property name=\"TestTimeout\" value=\"30000\" /> from .testsettings -->\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <!-- Replaces the CodeCoverage DataCollector from .testsettings -->\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n                     uri=\"datacollector://Microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n                     assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.CoverageCollectorDataCollector, Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector, Culture=neutral\">\n        <Configuration>\n          <CodeCoverage />\n        </Configuration>\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-32e0c05c3c62451e964aaa33200c5fb6/local.runsettings."}],"interactionId":"5fca55b7-6813-4840-92cc-6e7391bacbc5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has an MSTest v3 project with a `.testsettings` file. `.testsettings` files are not supported by MSTest v3 / the modern test platform. They need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file.\n\nLet me invoke the migrate-mstest-v1v2-to-v3 skill since it covers replacing `.testsettings` with `.runsettings`.\n\nActually, looking more carefully, the project already has MSTest 3.8.0, so they've already upgraded. The issue is just that the `.testsettings` file is being ignored. I should help them create a `.runsettings` file that captures the same configuration.\n\n\nI'll map the key settings from their `.testsettings` file: the 30-second test timeout needs to move into the MSTest section, the code coverage data collector configuration transfers to the DataCollectors section, and I can skip most of the assembly resolution settings since modern MSTest handles those automatically. Now I'll write out the equivalent `.runsettings` file.","outputTokens":766,"requestId":"0C01:14FF5F:62C9B7E:6C14FC0:69F01DB5"},"id":"0082740d-4925-401b-96a6-1e689db1678f","timestamp":"2026-04-28T02:38:59.645Z","parentId":"6ffe3484-a2f1-41b9-b799-3c4d141076db"}
